# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __index__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__index__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __index__.
# operator.index() requires __index__, which signals that an object can be
#   used as a lossless integer index (slice notation, bin()/hex()/oct()).
# __index__ is defined only on types that are exact integer representations
#   (int, bool, and their subclasses).
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state guards; even though Event.is_set()
#   returns bool and bool.__index__ is defined, asyncio.Event itself does not
#   define __index__ — the guard object is not an integer.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: encapsulate a counter but the counter
#   is not losslessly extractable as an int via __index__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; __index__ is not defined.
#   Task and Future represent pending asynchronous computations, not integers.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; qsize() is a method,
#   not __index__. The queue object cannot be used as a slice index.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

